title: Jeffbloo/fix dml rnn failures
body:
**Description**: 
The DML EP maintain maps between raw ORT KernelDef pointers and the functors used to create its own nodes within DML graph partitions.  This way, it can always let ORT manage resolving registrations, and have more shared code paths.

This was always inherently fragile, because it assumes the lifetime of KernelDefs exceeds that of the DML EP.  There's now a case where this isn’t true.  A separate issue of overlapping DML kernel registrations can result in map entries which key off a pointer that's freed.  This leads to problems for operators which are not expected to have entries in this map (RNN, GRU, LSTM, and ConstantOfShape), if they share an address with that freed pointer.

While addressing the underlying fragility will be nice, this is a scoped fix through better error checking.

**Motivation and Context**
This is believed to have caused sporadic failures with RNN models.  Some of the affected backend test cases were previously disabled, then the DML build was disabled after additional failures were encountered.

title: NCHWc: Handle Concat opset version 11
body:
**Description**:
The NCHWc optimization for Concat is not working for opset version 11 models because the list of expected domain versions was not updated.

**Motivation and Context**
Models built to opset version 11 won't have the Concat optimization to avoid extra tensor reorders without this change, so they will be slower than opset version 10.

The NCHWc unit test has been updated to use opset version 11 by default (an existing test already broke doing just this change). As a result of this change, the handling of Clip also needed to be updated.

title: resize: clear cache when moving to next channel
body:
**Description**: For cubic interpolation we use a 4x4 grid. There is a potential to cache the results during interpolation since there is an overlap when moving from position to position. However this cache is only valid for 2D .i.e H*W ... and it needs to be cleared when moving to the next channel. This PR clears the cache when moving to next channel. 

**Motivation and Context**
- Fixes a bug when running cubic interpolation in case of multi channel inputs

Add a new execution provider targeting Arm architecture based on Arm Compute Library.
Validated on NXP i.MX8QM CPU with ResNet50, MobileNetv2 and VGG models.

ACL vs CPU  	16%	9%	21%	13%

Usage documentation available in ACL-ExecutionProvider.

- Remove Memcpy node and kernel dependencies
- Move prints to verbose log
- Revert onnx external version change 
- Run clang-format

v4:
- Revert OPENMP multicore fix, no longer necessary
- Default to ACL 19.05

v3:
- Removed unused InsertFusedRules() function
- Removed redundant acl_provider_factory.h
- Moved createMemoryManager() function to acl_common.cc
- Enabled Pooling with ACL 
- Fixed tests feedback: enable_cpu_mem_arena initialization, ORT_UNUSED_PARAMETER

v2:
- integrated perf test
- integrated unit tests

- added documentation

title: Add FastGelu Cuda Op for Gelu and Add bias fusion
body:
**Description**: Cuda op of Gelu approximation with an optional bias input 

**Motivation and Context**

This op is used widely in transformer models like BERT etc. This cuda op significantly improves performance than the element-wise Gelu:
(1) Utilize half2 to optimize float16 inference.
(2) Optional fuse the Add bias.

For example, inference speed of a test model on same setting:
 Gelu: 15.4 ms
 FastGelu: 14.7 ms
 FastGelu with bias fused: 13.6 ms

title: [NupharEP] symbolic_shape_infer improvements
body:
**Description**: This change is to expand model support for Nuphar EP
- Improves symbolic shape inference in following ways:
1. Extend suggested merge to map to literals with --auto_merge. For example, MatMul of ['ax1', 'ax2'] x [128, 256] would now map 'ax2' to 128
2. Add --int_max option to simplify computations like Min(100000, 'dim') to be 'dim'. This helps ops like Slice to generate correct shape, i.e. start=0, end=Min(100000, dim - 2) on dim. It was previously treated as equal, since sympy cannot determine Min(100000, dim - 2) < dim.
- Fix a bug in create_shared script on Windows, that AOT dll is not generated because of failure in link, when there are too many obj files
- Some build warning fixes for NupharEP.

title: Add support for user defined data preprocess module/function
body:
This commit adds two command line options to calibrate.py and support for user defined data preprocessing module and function. 
1)	Options: 
a.	--data_preprocess – this option takes a string parameter in the format ‘module_name.function_name’. 
b.	--data_preprocess_filepath – this option takes a string parameter for path to the module. If it is omitted, the script will set it to the working directory.  
2)	Limitation:
a.	The data preprocessing function is required to take 3 arguments: image_filepath, height, and width.
